{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":678,"text":"One summer afternoon in 2013,"},{"time":3298,"text":"DC police detained, questioned\nand searched a man"},{"time":6450,"text":"who appeared suspicious\nand potentially dangerous."},{"time":10316,"text":"This wasn't what I was wearing\nthe day of the detention, to be fair,"},{"time":13785,"text":"but I have a picture of that as well."},{"time":15632,"text":"I know it's very frightening --\ntry to remain calm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18352,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":19469,"text":"At this time, I was interning"},{"time":21915,"text":"at the Public Defender Service\nin Washington DC,"},{"time":24671,"text":"and I was visiting\na police station for work."},{"time":27114,"text":"I was on my way out,"},{"time":28298,"text":"and before I could make it to my car,"},{"time":30314,"text":"two police cars pulled up\nto block my exit,"},{"time":32639,"text":"and an officer approached me from behind."},{"time":34994,"text":"He told me to stop, take my backpack off"},{"time":37290,"text":"and put my hands on the police car\nparked next to us."},{"time":40800,"text":"About a dozen officers\nthen gathered near us."},{"time":43819,"text":"All of them had handguns,"},{"time":45090,"text":"some had assault rifles."},{"time":46454,"text":"They rifled through my backpack."},{"time":48212,"text":"They patted me down."},{"time":49641,"text":"They took pictures of me\nspread on the police car,"},{"time":52026,"text":"and they laughed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53206,"text":"And as all this was happening --"},{"time":54770,"text":"as I was on the police car trying\nto ignore the shaking in my legs,"},{"time":58044,"text":"trying to think clearly\nabout what I should do --"},{"time":60403,"text":"something stuck out to me as odd."},{"time":62426,"text":"When I look at myself in this photo,"},{"time":64444,"text":"if I were to describe myself,"},{"time":66303,"text":"I think I'd say something like,"},{"time":68114,"text":"\"19-year-old Indian male,\nbright T-shirt, wearing glasses.\""},{"time":73527,"text":"But they weren't including\nany of these details."},{"time":75832,"text":"Into their police radios\nas they described me,"},{"time":78106,"text":"they kept saying, \"Middle Eastern\nmale with a backpack."},{"time":80762,"text":"Middle Eastern male with a backpack.\""},{"time":82815,"text":"And this description carried on\ninto their police reports."},{"time":86419,"text":"I never expected to be described\nby my own government in these terms:"},{"time":91049,"text":"\"lurking,\""},{"time":93301,"text":"\"nefarious,\""},{"time":95832,"text":"\"terrorist.\""},{"time":97016,"text":"And the detention dragged on like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98983,"text":"They sent dogs trained to smell explosives\nto sweep the area I'd been in."},{"time":102885,"text":"They called the federal government\nto see if I was on any watch lists."},{"time":106336,"text":"They sent a couple of detectives\nto cross-examine me on why,"},{"time":109211,"text":"if I claimed I had nothing to hide,"},{"time":111351,"text":"I wouldn't consent to a search of my car."},{"time":113421,"text":"And I could see\nthey weren't happy with me,"},{"time":115506,"text":"but I felt I had no way of knowing\nwhat they'd want to do next."},{"time":118613,"text":"At one point, the officer\nwho patted me down"},{"time":121534,"text":"scanned the side of the police station\nto see where the security camera was"},{"time":125088,"text":"to see how much of this\nwas being recorded."},{"time":127984,"text":"And when he did that,"},{"time":129176,"text":"it really sank in how completely\nI was at their mercy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132670,"text":"I think we're all normalized\nfrom a young age"},{"time":135117,"text":"to the idea of police officers\nand arrests and handcuffs,"},{"time":138894,"text":"so it's easy to forget how demeaning\nand coercive a thing it is"},{"time":142860,"text":"to seize control over\nanother person's body."},{"time":145789,"text":"I know it sounds like\nthe point of my story"},{"time":147858,"text":"is how badly treated I was\nbecause of my race --"},{"time":150324,"text":"and yes, I don't think I would've been\ndetained if I were white."},{"time":153468,"text":"But actually, what I have in mind\ntoday is something else."},{"time":156231,"text":"What I have in mind is how\nmuch worse things might've been"},{"time":158973,"text":"if I weren't affluent."},{"time":160161,"text":"I mean, they thought I might be trying\nto plant an explosive,"},{"time":163103,"text":"and they investigated that possibility\nfor an hour and a half,"},{"time":166296,"text":"but I was never put in handcuffs,"},{"time":168032,"text":"I was never taken to a jail cell."},{"time":170068,"text":"I think if I were from one of Washington\nDC's poor communities of color,"},{"time":174152,"text":"and they thought I was\nendangering officers' lives,"},{"time":176599,"text":"things might've ended differently."},{"time":178244,"text":"And in fact, in our system, I think\nit's better to be an affluent person"},{"time":181672,"text":"suspected of trying\nto blow up a police station"},{"time":183984,"text":"than it is to be a poor person"},{"time":185675,"text":"who's suspected of much,\nmuch less than this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188356,"text":"I want to give you an example\nfrom my current work."},{"time":191309,"text":"Right now, I'm working\nat a civil rights organization in DC,"},{"time":194583,"text":"called Equal Justice Under Law."},{"time":196939,"text":"Let me start by asking you all a question."},{"time":199872,"text":"How many of you have ever gotten\na parking ticket in your life?"},{"time":202883,"text":"Raise your hand."},{"time":204071,"text":"Yeah. So have I."},{"time":206041,"text":"And when I had to pay it,"},{"time":207398,"text":"it felt annoying and it felt bad,"},{"time":209453,"text":"but I paid it and I moved on."},{"time":211393,"text":"I'm guessing most of you\nhave paid your tickets as well."},{"time":214616,"text":"But what would happen if you\ncouldn't afford the amount on the ticket"},{"time":218927,"text":"and your family doesn't have\nthe money either, what happens then?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":222121,"text":"Well, one thing that's not supposed\nto happen under the law is,"},{"time":225136,"text":"you're not supposed to be\narrested and jailed"},{"time":227264,"text":"simply because you can't afford to pay."},{"time":229384,"text":"That's illegal under federal law."},{"time":231212,"text":"But that's what local governments\nacross the country are doing"},{"time":234164,"text":"to people who are poor."},{"time":235345,"text":"And so many of our lawsuits\nat Equal Justice Under Law"},{"time":238289,"text":"target these modern-day debtors' prisons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241771,"text":"One of our cases is against\nFerguson, Missouri."},{"time":244516,"text":"And I know when I say Ferguson,"},{"time":246364,"text":"many of you will think of police violence."},{"time":248486,"text":"But today I want to talk\nabout a different aspect"},{"time":250797,"text":"of the relationship between\ntheir police force and their citizens."},{"time":254287,"text":"Ferguson was issuing an average\nof over two arrest warrants,"},{"time":257845,"text":"per person, per year,"},{"time":259876,"text":"mostly for unpaid debt to the courts."},{"time":262996,"text":"When I imagine what that would feel like\nif, every time I left my house,"},{"time":267043,"text":"there was a chance a police officer\nwould run my license plate,"},{"time":270167,"text":"see a warrant for unpaid debt,"},{"time":271882,"text":"seize my body they way the did in DC"},{"time":274036,"text":"and then take me to a jail cell,"},{"time":275977,"text":"I feel a little sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278838,"text":"I've met many of the people in Ferguson\nwho have experienced this,"},{"time":282018,"text":"and I've heard some of their stories."},{"time":283829,"text":"In Ferguson's jail,"},{"time":285221,"text":"in each small cell,\nthere's a bunk bed and a toilet,"},{"time":288354,"text":"but they'd pack four people\ninto each cell."},{"time":290680,"text":"So there'd be two people on the bunks\nand two people on the floor,"},{"time":293819,"text":"one with nowhere to go except\nright next to the filthy toilet,"},{"time":296770,"text":"which was never cleaned."},{"time":297954,"text":"In fact, the whole cell was never cleaned,"},{"time":300141,"text":"so the floor and the walls were lined\nwith blood and mucus."},{"time":304088,"text":"No water to drink,"},{"time":305262,"text":"except coming out of a spigot\nconnected to the toilet."},{"time":307990,"text":"The water looked and tasted dirty,"},{"time":309734,"text":"there was never enough food,"},{"time":311273,"text":"never any showers,"},{"time":312845,"text":"women menstruating\nwithout any hygiene products,"},{"time":315659,"text":"no medical attention whatsoever."},{"time":317377,"text":"When I asked a woman\nabout medical attention,"},{"time":319581,"text":"she laughed, and she said, \"Oh, no, no."},{"time":322000,"text":"The only attention you get\nfrom the guards in there is sexual.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":325838,"text":"So, they'd take the debtors\nto this place and they'd say,"},{"time":328582,"text":"\"We're not letting you leave\nuntil you make a payment on your debt.\""},{"time":332142,"text":"And if you could -- if you\ncould call a family member"},{"time":334796,"text":"who could somehow come up with some money,"},{"time":336961,"text":"then maybe you were out."},{"time":338378,"text":"If it was enough money, you were out."},{"time":340561,"text":"But if it wasn't, you'd stay there\nfor days or weeks,"},{"time":343903,"text":"and every day the guards\nwould come down to the cells"},{"time":346713,"text":"and haggle with the debtors\nabout the price of release that day."},{"time":350625,"text":"You'd stay until, at some point,\nthe jail would be booked to capacity,"},{"time":354771,"text":"and they'd want to book someone new in."},{"time":356745,"text":"And at that point, they'd think,"},{"time":358330,"text":"\"OK, it's unlikely this person\ncan come up with the money,"},{"time":361109,"text":"it's more likely this new person will.\""},{"time":362993,"text":"You're out, they're in,\nand the machine kept moving like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365995,"text":"I met a man who,"},{"time":368045,"text":"nine years ago, was arrested\nfor panhandling in a Walgreens."},{"time":372336,"text":"He couldn't afford his fines\nand his court fees from that case."},{"time":376416,"text":"When he was young\nhe survived a house fire,"},{"time":379436,"text":"only because he jumped out\nof the third-story window to escape."},{"time":382433,"text":"But that fall left him\nwith damage to his brain"},{"time":384658,"text":"and several parts of this body,\nincluding his leg."},{"time":387117,"text":"So he can't work,"},{"time":388300,"text":"and he relies on social security\npayments to survive."},{"time":390826,"text":"When I met him in his apartment,"},{"time":392536,"text":"he had nothing of value there --\nnot even food in his fridge."},{"time":395439,"text":"He's chronically hungry."},{"time":396628,"text":"He had nothing of value in his apartment\nexcept a small piece of cardboard"},{"time":400131,"text":"on which he'd written\nthe names of his children."},{"time":402389,"text":"He cherished this a lot.\nHe was happy to show it to me."},{"time":404991,"text":"But he can't pay his fines and fees\nbecause he has nothing to give."},{"time":408175,"text":"In the last nine years,\nhe's been arrested 13 times,"},{"time":411565,"text":"and jailed for a total of 130 days\non that panhandling case."},{"time":416659,"text":"One of those stretches lasted 45 days."},{"time":419731,"text":"Just imagine spending from right now\nuntil sometime in June"},{"time":424161,"text":"in the place that I described to you\na few moments ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428616,"text":"He told me about all the suicide attempts\nhe's seen in Ferguson's jail;"},{"time":432721,"text":"about the time a man found\na way to hang himself"},{"time":435018,"text":"out of reach of the other inmates,"},{"time":436702,"text":"so all they could do\nwas yell and yell and yell,"},{"time":439888,"text":"trying to get the guards' attention"},{"time":441652,"text":"so they could come down and cut him down."},{"time":443669,"text":"And he told me that it took the guards\nover five minutes to respond,"},{"time":447129,"text":"and when they came,\nthe man was unconscious."},{"time":449421,"text":"So they called the paramedics\nand the paramedics went to the cell."},{"time":452616,"text":"They said, \"He'll be OK,\""},{"time":453972,"text":"so they just left him there on the floor."},{"time":456200,"text":"I heard many stories like this\nand they shouldn't have surprised me,"},{"time":459518,"text":"because suicide is the single leading\ncause of death in our local jails."},{"time":463852,"text":"This is related to the lack\nof mental health care in our jails."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466863,"text":"I met a woman, single mother of three,\nmaking seven dollars an hour."},{"time":470807,"text":"She relies on food stamps\nto feed herself and her children."},{"time":474108,"text":"About a decade ago,"},{"time":475676,"text":"she got a couple of traffic tickets\nand a minor theft charge,"},{"time":479465,"text":"and she can't afford her fines\nand fees on those cases."},{"time":482726,"text":"Since then, she's been jailed\nabout 10 times on those cases,"},{"time":486250,"text":"but she has schizophrenia\nand bipolar disorder,"},{"time":488557,"text":"and she needs medication every day."},{"time":490732,"text":"She doesn't have access\nto those medications in Ferguson's jail,"},{"time":493794,"text":"because no one has access\nto their medications."},{"time":496034,"text":"She told me about what it was like\nto spend two weeks in a cage,"},{"time":500084,"text":"hallucinating people and shadows\nand hearing voices,"},{"time":503661,"text":"begging for the medication\nthat would make it all stop,"},{"time":506279,"text":"only to be ignored."},{"time":508370,"text":"And this isn't anomalous, either:"},{"time":510240,"text":"thirty percent of women in our local jails\nhave serious mental health needs"},{"time":513789,"text":"just like hers,"},{"time":514969,"text":"but only one in six receives\nany mental health care while in jail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519510,"text":"And so, I heard all these stories\nabout this grotesque dungeon"},{"time":523359,"text":"that Ferguson was operating\nfor its debtors,"},{"time":525581,"text":"and when it came time\nfor me to actually see it"},{"time":527898,"text":"and to go visit Ferguson's jail,"},{"time":529876,"text":"I'm not sure what I was expecting to see,"},{"time":531940,"text":"but I wasn't expecting this."},{"time":534495,"text":"It's an ordinary government building."},{"time":536358,"text":"It could be a post office or a school."},{"time":538838,"text":"It reminded me that these illegal\nextortion schemes"},{"time":542554,"text":"aren't being run somewhere in the shadows,"},{"time":544666,"text":"they're being run out in the open\nby our public officials."},{"time":547406,"text":"They're a matter of public policy."},{"time":549130,"text":"And this reminded me\nthat poverty jailing in general,"},{"time":551993,"text":"even outside the debtors' prison context,"},{"time":554225,"text":"plays a very visible and central role\nin our justice system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557818,"text":"What I have in mind is our policy of bail."},{"time":560054,"text":"In our system, whether\nyou're detained or free,"},{"time":562630,"text":"pending trial is not a matter\nof how dangerous you are"},{"time":565784,"text":"or how much of a flight risk you pose."},{"time":568056,"text":"It's a matter of whether you can afford\nto post your bail amount."},{"time":571166,"text":"So Bill Cosby, whose bail\nwas set at a million dollars,"},{"time":573902,"text":"immediately writes the check,\nand doesn't spend a second in a jail cell."},{"time":577386,"text":"But Sandra Bland, who died in jail,"},{"time":579142,"text":"was only there because her family\nwas unable to come up with 500 dollars."},{"time":583164,"text":"In fact, there are half a million\nSandra Blands across the country --"},{"time":586575,"text":"500,000 people who are in jail right now,"},{"time":588865,"text":"only because they can't afford\ntheir bail amount."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591550,"text":"We're told that our jails\nare places for criminals,"},{"time":594631,"text":"but statistically that's not the case:"},{"time":596668,"text":"three out of every five people\nin jail right now are there pretrial."},{"time":600993,"text":"They haven't been convicted of any crime;"},{"time":603199,"text":"they haven't pled guilty to any offense."},{"time":606351,"text":"Right here in San Francisco,"},{"time":607719,"text":"85 percent of the inmates\nin our jail in San Francisco"},{"time":611133,"text":"are pretrial detainees."},{"time":612901,"text":"This means San Francisco is spending\nsomething like 80 million dollars"},{"time":616310,"text":"every year"},{"time":617504,"text":"to fund pretrial detention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621240,"text":"Many of these people who are in jail\nonly because they can't post bail"},{"time":625683,"text":"are facing allegations so minor"},{"time":627953,"text":"that the amount of time it would take\nfor them to sit waiting for trial"},{"time":631360,"text":"is longer than the sentence\nthey would receive if convicted,"},{"time":634436,"text":"which means they're guaranteed\nto get out faster"},{"time":636728,"text":"if they just plead guilty."},{"time":638036,"text":"So now the choice is:"},{"time":639619,"text":"Should I stay here in this horrible place,"},{"time":642516,"text":"away from my family and my dependents,"},{"time":644650,"text":"almost guaranteed to lose my job,"},{"time":647151,"text":"and then fight the charges?"},{"time":648796,"text":"Or should I just plead guilty to whatever\nthe prosecutor wants and get out?"},{"time":652389,"text":"And at this point, they're pretrial\ndetainees, not criminals."},{"time":655348,"text":"But once they take that plea deal,\nwe'll call them criminals,"},{"time":658264,"text":"even though an affluent person\nwould never have been in this situation,"},{"time":661668,"text":"because an affluent person\nwould have simply been bailed out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664566,"text":"At this point you might be wondering,"},{"time":666680,"text":"\"This guy's in the inspiration section,\nwhat is he doing --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":669498,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":670682,"text":"\"This is extremely depressing.\nI want my money back.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":673512,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":674742,"text":"But in actuality,"},{"time":677165,"text":"I find talking about jailing much less\ndepressing than the alternative,"},{"time":681579,"text":"because I think if we don't talk\nabout these issues"},{"time":684039,"text":"and collectively change\nhow we think about jailing,"},{"time":686464,"text":"at the end of all of our lives,"},{"time":687992,"text":"we'll still have jails full of poor people\nwho don't belong there."},{"time":691147,"text":"That really is depressing to me."},{"time":692725,"text":"But what's exciting to me is the thought\nthat these stories can move us"},{"time":696173,"text":"to think about jailing in different terms."},{"time":698240,"text":"Not in sterile policy terms\nlike \"mass incarceration,\""},{"time":701635,"text":"or \"sentencing of nonviolent offenders,\""},{"time":703645,"text":"but in human terms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704835,"text":"When we put a human being in a cage\nfor days or weeks or months"},{"time":709444,"text":"or even years,"},{"time":710912,"text":"what are we doing\nto that person's mind and body?"},{"time":713285,"text":"Under what conditions\nare we really willing to do that?"},{"time":716569,"text":"And so if starting with a few\nhundred of us in this room,"},{"time":719399,"text":"we can commit to thinking about\njailing in this different light,"},{"time":722467,"text":"then we can undo that normalization\nI was referring to earlier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725971,"text":"If I leave you with anything today,\nI hope it's with the thought"},{"time":729033,"text":"that if we want anything\nto fundamentally change --"},{"time":731489,"text":"not just to reform our policies\non bail and fines and fees --"},{"time":734793,"text":"but also to make sure that whatever\nnew policies replace those"},{"time":737870,"text":"don't punish the poor and the marginalized\nin their own new way."},{"time":740945,"text":"If we want that kind of change,"},{"time":742601,"text":"then this shift in thinking\nis required of each of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745150,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746358,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}